{
  "texts": [
    "There will generally be some range of generalization where algorithmic fidelity can be said to \"transfer\" to similar populations.",
    "But it will not be entirely clear exactly how similar is similar enough.",
    "It will of course always be better to assess algorithmic fidelity in the most similar population that it is feasible to study.",
    "Algorithmic fidelity evaluation is useful here as a way to establish validity precisely because it was not used as an optimization target.",
    "If the evaluation instead became the objective then it would not only fail by virtue of Goodhart's law (ie., \"When a measure becomes a target, it ceases to be a good measure."
  ]
}